cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.AI 

This paper deals with logics and their expressive power, which falls under the category of mathematical logic (cs.LO). The use of monoid and groupoid word-problems and regular and context-free languages suggests a connection to formal language theory (cs.FL). The mention of computational classification and characterizing ATIME(n) suggests a connection to complexity theory (cs.DS). The study of quantifiers and their expressive power also suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the use of logic in characterizing computational problems suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
